    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>The state or characteristic of having a high degree of distinctness in an image. Examples are images achieved through the spacing of individual optical elements, such as grains of light-sensitive chemicals in a photograph or pixels in an electronic image.</Note_Text>
